      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Roast the Garlic - Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Cut the top off the garlic bulb to expose the cloves. Drizzle with olive oil, wrap it in foil, and roast for about 30 minutes or until the cloves are soft and golden. Allow it to cool, then squeeze the roasted garlic cloves out of the bulb.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Roast the Cauliflower - On a baking sheet, toss the cauliflower florets with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until they’re tender and have a golden color. Remove from the oven and set aside.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Start the Soup - In a large pot, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and sauté until it’s translucent and fragrant.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the Roasted Garlic - Stir in the roasted garlic from step 1. This will infuse the soup with a rich, roasted garlic flavor.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Blend the Mixture - Add the roasted cauliflower florets to the pot and stir to combine.Pour in the chicken or vegetable broth and bring the mixture to a simmer. Let it simmer for about 10-15 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Blend the Soup - Using an immersion blender or a regular blender (in batches), blend the mixture until smooth and creamy.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the Cheese - Return the blended mixture to the pot and stir in the milk and shredded cheddar cheese. Continue to cook over low heat, stirring, until the cheese is fully melted and the soup is heated through.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Season and Serve - Taste the soup and adjust the seasoning with salt and black pepper, as needed. Ladle the soup into bowls and garnish with additional shredded cheddar cheese, chopped chives or green onions, and crispy bacon bits, if desired.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Add salt a pinch at a time, tasting. If still flat, finish with a squeeze of lemon or a splash of vinegar to lift it.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned, or the aromatics weren't sweated long enough.",
              "symptom": "The soup tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stir cream in off the heat, or use crème fraîche, which doesn't split. Don't reboil after adding.",
              "cause": "Dairy added at too high a heat, or left to simmer after.",
              "symptom": "Cream-based soup splits"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Loosen with hot stock or water, a ladle at a time, until it pours from the spoon in a ribbon.",
              "cause": "Reduced too far, or the starch in the veg sets up on cooling.",
              "symptom": "Blended soup is too thick"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Simmer uncovered to reduce, or blitz in another roasted veg (potato, parsnip) to thicken.",
              "cause": "Stock-to-veg ratio too high.",
              "symptom": "Blended soup is too thin"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegan version: swap dairy cream for cashew cream (soak 100 g cashews in hot water, blend smooth) or oat cream.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Smokier finish: stir in a teaspoon of smoked paprika at the end, or top with crispy chorizo.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a day ahead; the flavour deepens overnight in the fridge.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
